{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pulls/55", "html_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/55", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/55.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/55.patch", "merged_at": "2020-01-18T23:50:17Z"}, "body": "~~Note that this PR should await a new major stable `reqwest` release before being merged. It should not be long. But I'm creating the PR anyway so that the essential parts can be reviewed.~~\r\n\r\nThe PR is now ready.\r\n\r\nLib upgrades:\r\n* Requires Rust 1.39.0 for async/await syntax\r\n* Upgrades tokio to 0.2\r\n* Upgrades hyper to 0.13\r\n* Upgrades reqwest to 0.10\r\n\r\nAPI breaking changes:\r\n~~`pact_consumer`: `trait StartMockServer` + `trait ValidatingMockServer`.~~\r\n\r\n~~I've tried my best to make consumer tests work nicely with the recently released `tokio-0.2`. As the mock server itself is implemented asynchronously, I feel that it's correct to publicly expose its async interface, and make it compatible with the `[tokio::test]` macro. An publicly asynchronous mock server needs to be shut down explicitly, which I tried to make clear in the docs.~~\r\n\r\nRemoved `StartMockServer::create_mock_server`\r\n\r\nThere is no longer any support for starting the `pact_consumer` mock server asynchronously. This idea of mine was flawed. It's now instead always run in a separate thread. Implementation inspired by https://github.com/seanmonstar/reqwest/blob/master/tests/support/server.rs.\r\n\r\nThis is good because it makes that API completely tokio-independent (no `async` functions exposed).\r\n\r\nFixes #51 ", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/55/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/55/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/53", "id": 524058936, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzQxOTA1OTU3", "number": 53, "title": "Update to Rust 2018 edition", "user": {"login": "audunhalland", "id": 5767935, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU3Njc5MzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5767935?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland", "html_url": "https://github.com/audunhalland", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/audunhalland/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-11-17T22:33:38Z", "updated_at": "2019-11-24T04:22:30Z", "closed_at": "2019-11-24T04:22:30Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "type": null, "active_lock_reason": null, "draft": false, "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pulls/53", "html_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/53", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/53.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/53.patch", "merged_at": "2019-11-24T04:22:30Z"}, "body": "The Rust 2018 edition removes the need to specify `extern crate`, and supports scoped macros, which I tend to like, especially for log statements: `log::info!(...)`. Also, the macro imports can be declared closer to the code that uses the macros (instead of a `macro_use` at the crate root), increasing code readability.\r\n\r\nSome upgrades here and there (`log` needs to be at version 0.4 for scoped macro usage).\r\n\r\nFixes #52 ", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/53/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/50", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/50/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/50/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pact-foundation/pact-reference/issues/50/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pact-foundation/pact-reference/pull/50", "id": 503143931, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzI1MDYyODgy", "number": 50, "title": "Allow to recreate mock-server", "user": {"login": "jdemeule", "id": 16181379, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTg